{
  "abstract": "Pigeonpea (Cajanus cajan (L.) Millsp.) – a major pulse crop of India and other tropical major pulse crop of India and other tropical yield due to wilt disease, caused by Fusariumudum. Several attempts have been made to control this disease using cultural and host- plant resistant methods. Fungicides, have not been found to give adequate protection against Fusarium wilts, so far (Lemanceau and Alabouvette, 1993).\r\n",
